terrible /ˈtɛrəbəl/

1. ADJ A terrible experience or situation is very bad or very unpleasant. 可怕的 

例： Tens of thousands more suffered terrible injuries in the world's worst industrial disaster. 还有数万人在这场世界最严重的工业灾难中受了重伤。 

例： I often have terrible nightmares. 我经常做可怕的恶梦。 

2. terribly ADV 可怕地 [ADV after v] 

例： My son has suffered terribly. He has lost his best friend. 我儿子遭受了可怕的打击，失去了最好的朋友。 

3. ADJ If something is terrible , it is very bad or of very poor quality. 糟糕的; 劣质的 

例： She admits her French is terrible. 她承认自己的法语很糟糕。 

4. ADJ You use terrible to emphasize the great extent or degree of something. (程度) 十足的 [ADJ n] [强调] 

例： I was a terrible fool, you know. 你知道，我那时是个十足的傻瓜。 

5. terribly ADV 非常 

例： I'm terribly sorry to bother you at this hour. 我非常抱歉这个时候来打搅您。

